THE Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Ministerial Task Team on Traffic Control, on Wednesday, demolished illegal toilet structures at the Nyanya market and besides the bridge on Jikwoyi road, the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) has reported. Addressing newsmen shortly after the demolition, chairman of the team, Mr Ikharo Attah, said the measure was part of efforts to rid the Nyanya road of traffic congestion with a view to easing movement of commuters. ALSO READ: Edo govt begins removal of illegal structures Attah said erecting structures within the market near Nyanya Bridge was against the Abuja Master Plan and Development Control Regulations. He warned marketers and investors in the area to always seek approval from FCT Development Control and other relevant agencies before building any structure.